const cwd = "/Users/zchee/go/src/github.com/zchee/spanner-manager";
const msg = `Avoid reparsing NEW_UUID() in diff hot paths

The diff helper rebuilt the AST for NEW_UUID() on every UUID default
lookup, which matched the PR review concern on a path exercised heavily
during schema comparisons. This switches that parsing to sync.OnceValues
and adds a regression test that proves the parsed expression instance is
reused without changing rendered SQL.

Constraint: Keep the fix limited to the reviewed NEW_UUID() parse hotspot in diff/diff.go
Rejected: Add a broader default-expression cache abstraction | unnecessary for the single reviewed constant path
Confidence: high
Scope-risk: narrow
Reversibility: clean
Directive: If future callers need mutable AST defaults, clone the cached expression before mutation instead of editing the shared instance
Tested: git diff --check; go test ./diff -run 'TestDiff_HelperCoverage/(defaultByScalarTypeName|uuidDefaultExpr reuses parsed expression)' -count=1
Not-tested: Full repo test suite in the commit step

Co-authored-by: Codex <noreply@openai.com>
`;
