// @exec: {"yield_time_ms": 10000, "max_output_tokens": 12000}
const cwd = "/Users/zchee/go/src/github.com/zchee/spanner-manager";
const msg = `Keep import-block parsing stable when comments contain parentheses

The generator merged header/body templates by scanning rendered import
blocks, but the old depth logic counted parentheses everywhere on the
line. That made comments like \`import ( // )\` look like the block ended
early. This change makes the import scanner ignore parentheses inside
comments and quoted literals, and extends the legacy-template regression
to lock the reported edge case.

Constraint: Fix only the reviewed import-block depth bug without broad parser refactors
